'''Presentity''' is an [[entity]] described by [[presence information]]. The word is a combination of words "presence" and "entity" and was first introduced in [[change request|RFC]] 2778. Originally it was defined as entity which provides presence information.

Presentity usually refers to a [[human]]. In this case presence information describes availability and willingnes of this human to [[communication|communicate]] via set of communication services. For example users of the [[instant messaging|instant messenger]] [[ICQ]] are presentities and their presence information is ICQ user status (online, offline, away, etc.).

A presentity can also refer to a group of humans, for example a collection of customer service agents in a [[call centre|call center]]. This presentity may be considered availabile if there is at least one agent ready to accept a call.

